def: One of a class of paupers or pensioners, or licensed beggars,in Scotland, to whim annually on the king's birthday were distributedcertain alms, including a blue gown; a beadsman.
After the manner of ambrosia; delightfully. "Smeltambrosially." Tennyson.
Belonging to, or relating to, the East Indies.-- n.
One of the half ribs against the walls in a ceiling vaultedwith ribs.
A sense organ found in certain sponges. It consists of severalfilaments, each of which arises from a single cell.
One who infracts or infringes; a violator; a breaker.
Full of barm or froth; in a ferment. "Barmy beer." Dryden.
The Brazilian porcupine (Cercolades, or Sphingurus,prehensiles), remarkable for its prehensile tail.
Of or pertaining to the Gastropoda.
Capacity for religious affections or worship.
